# Xcode signing — team IDs and helpers

## Do not hardcode personal or foreign teams

- **Never** commit **`DEVELOPMENT_TEAM = …`** (Apple team ID) unless **every** contributor is on that team and the repo explicitly documents it.
- If a clone shows *No Account for Team "XXXXXXXXXX"*, remove the pinned team from **`project.pbxproj`** for the **app** target (Debug/Release) so **Signing & Capabilities** uses the developer’s local team.
- **Do not** reintroduce historical IDs from old branches; use **`PM529U3B66`** only if it is the project’s agreed shared team.

## Auxiliary targets (dylibs, `RootHelper`, internal tools)

- If the target is **not** a shipped, independently signed product, prefer **`CODE_SIGNING_ALLOWED = NO`**, **`CODE_SIGNING_REQUIRED = NO`**, **`CODE_SIGN_IDENTITY = ""`**, and **no** `DEVELOPMENT_TEAM` so **unsigned / CI** builds do not require that team’s **Development** certificate.
- Re-enable automatic signing only when you intentionally distribute a signed helper.

## CI / verification

- Unsigned smoke build: **`CODE_SIGNING_ALLOWED=NO`** on **`xcodebuild`** (see [LESSONS_LEARNED.md](../../LESSONS_LEARNED.md) §18).
- Narrative: [LESSONS_LEARNED.md](../../LESSONS_LEARNED.md) §19–20, §24–26. Checklist skill: [tv-safari-xcode-signing/SKILL.md](../skills/tv-safari-xcode-signing/SKILL.md).
- Project-level signing hygiene: [xcode-pbxproj-signing-hygiene.mdc](xcode-pbxproj-signing-hygiene.mdc).
